CAPE TOWN &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba told parliament on Tuesday the main budget deficit in 2016/17 narrowed to 3.8% of gross domestic product (GDP) from a previous estimate of 3.9% and would decrease further in coming years.&#8220;Over the next three years the deficit will be reduced to 3.3%, stabilising debt as a percentage of GDP and confirming the resilience of our public finances,&#8221; Gigaba said in a televised speech. 